.TH "dwc2_hc_write_packet" 9 "dwc2_hc_write_packet" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dwc2_hc_write_packet \- Writes a packet into the Tx FIFO associated with the Host Channel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" dwc2_hc_write_packet
.BI "(struct dwc2_hsotg *hsotg "  ","
.BI "struct dwc2_host_chan *chan "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hsotg" 12
Programming view of DWC_otg controller
.IP "chan" 12
Information needed to initialize the host channel
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function should only be called in Slave mode. For a channel associated
with a non-periodic EP, the non-periodic Tx FIFO is written. For a channel
associated with a periodic EP, the periodic Tx FIFO is written.

Upon return the xfer_buf and xfer_count fields in chan are incremented by
the number of bytes written to the Tx FIFO.
